FRESH SUSHI. Expensive, but incredibly high grade sushi. It gets busy during lunch time, so call ahead and make a reservation, especially for the bar. Note, there is no menu for the sushi bar, so be ready to call out your favorite sashimi.

Hands down my favorite sushi spot. The fish is very fresh and they have a lot of variety. It's more of a traditional sushi spot so you won't find a lot of cut and hand rolls. The sweet shrimp is my favorite. I would also recommend the sashimi deluxe if you wanna try out different things, it's a big portion, good for two people.

My wife and I got lunch here and it was absolutely delightful. The 7 piece sushi special was a great price for the quality of the sushi. Even in an area spoiled with excellent sushi, this place stands out.

Kiriko is the treasure of Sawtelle Blvd. Their attention to detail makes everything taste better than you thought it could. Even their tempura tastes special. I highly recommend their 5 salmon sashimi sampler and their spinach and mushroom salad.
